3.2.3 Computation of Nodes and Weights
Except for the Chebyshev case (see Sect. 3.4), the explicit expressions of the nodes and weights of the general Jacobi-Gauss quadrature are not available, so they have to be computed by numerical means. An efﬁcient algorithm is to use the eigenvalue method described in Theorems 3.4 and 3.6.

